SIMPLE: lowly
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lowly
<hw>Low"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Lowlier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Lowliest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[<ets>Low</ets>, <pos>a.</pos> +
<ets>-ly</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not high; not elevated in place;
low.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Lowly</xex> lands.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Low in rank or social importance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One common right the great and <qex>lowly</qex> claims.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not lofty or sublime; humble.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These rural poems, and their <qex>lowly</qex> strain.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Having a low esteem of one's own worth; humble;
meek; free from pride.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Take my yoke upon you, and learn of me, for I am meek and
<qex>lowly</qex> in heart.</q> <rj><qau>Matt. xi. 29.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lowly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Lowly
<hw>Low"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a low manner;
humbly; meekly; modestly.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Be <xex>lowly</xex> wise.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In a low condition; meanly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will show myself highly fed, and <qex>lowly</qex> taught.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>low-lying</ent>⟦br⟧
